ala Mandir (B); 6 pm: Bijoy Sangeet Academy presents Arohan  an evening of classical music and dance. Participants: Sourav Chatterjee (santoor), Biswajit Roy Chowdhury (violin) and Sanatan Goswami (harmonium) in duet, Mahananda Kanjilal (Kathak) and Pandit Arun Bhaduri (vocal).				 																																	 June 18 at Gorky Sadan; 7 pm: Womens Interlink Foundation presents a charity show in aid of Nijoloy, a home for rescued, trafficked and orphaned girl children of AIDS victims. Featuring popular music concert by Lopamudra Mitra, Rabindrasangeet by Dr Ananda Gupta, and a collage of dance with music and poetry by Alokananda Roy. Inaugural lighting of the lamp by city police chief Sujoy Chakraborty, actress Rituparna Sengupta, vice-consul of German consulate Schwering , CWC chairperson Neelima Krishnamurthy and others.				 																																	 June 20 at Sisir Mancha; 6.30 pm: Sisikshu, a centre for training in recitation, will present its annual programme with recitation and reading of Hing Ting Chhat and Manchitra.				 																TALK				 																																	 June 18 at Seagull Bookstore, 31A S.P. Mukherjee Road; 5 pm: The Seagull Foundation for the Arts presents an evening with Dilip Simeon and Dr Purushottam Agarwal. Simeon will speak on The continuing significance of Truth and Ahimsa in our times. Agarwal will present a talk on Identity, Citizenship and Literature (Asmita, Nagarikta aur Sahitya).				 																																	 June 18 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Shivananda Hall; 6 pm: Sitanath Goswami will speak in Sanskrit on Bhagavad-Gita.				 																																	 Till June 18 at G.D. Birla Sabhagar; 4.30 pm - 8 pm: Bhagwath Saptah  Talks by Sw. Advaitananda of Chinmaya Mission.				 																																	 June 18 at Ramakrishna Vedanta Math, Raja Rajkrishna Street; 7 pm: Dr Sasanka Bhusan Bandyopadhyay will speak on Brihadaranyaka Upanishad.				 																BOOKS				 			